    "body": "### Problem\n\nLike the description says, `g:clipboard` can only be set once. The variable itself is updated but the changed code is not executed. \r\n\r\nNOTE: settings `set clipboard=unnamedplus` also stops the `g:clipboard` from updating, and this together with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/29634, makes it impossible to Neovide to setup a remote clipboard if the user configuration specifies `clipboard=unnamedplus`.\r\n\r\nA third way to make it stop working is to use the clipboard before setting `g:clipboard`\r\n\r\nNOTE: I tested down to Neovim 0.8, and all versions are broken.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a file named `clipboard.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal function set_clipboard(register)\r\n    return function(lines)\r\n    end\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal function get_clipboard(register)\r\n    return function()\r\n        return {{\"something..\"..math.random()}, \"V\"}\r\n    end\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.g.clipboard = {\r\n    name = \"neovide\",\r\n    copy = {\r\n        [\"+\"] = set_clipboard(\"+\"),\r\n        [\"*\"] = set_clipboard(\"*\"),\r\n    },\r\n    paste = {\r\n        [\"+\"] = get_clipboard(\"+\"),\r\n        [\"*\"] = get_clipboard(\"*\"),\r\n    },\r\n    cache = false,\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlternative 1.\r\n1. Launch nvim\r\n2. `:luafile clipboard.lua`\r\n3. `\"+p` -> pastes correctly\r\n4. Change `something` to `something else` in `clipboard.lua`\r\n5. `\"+p` -> Does still paste `something...`\r\n\r\nAlternative 2.\r\n1. Launch nvim\r\n2. `:set clipboard=unnamedplus`\r\n3. `:luafile clipboard.lua`\r\n4. `\"+p` -> Uses the system clipboard instead of our custom clipboard function\r\n\r\nAlternative 3.\r\n1. Launch nvim\r\n2. Paste something from the system clipboard\r\n3. `:luafile clipboard.lua`\r\n4. `\"+p` -> Still uses the system clipboard\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe clipboard should update each time it is set.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nManually built",
